ig) \\le C\\exp{\\big[-c(\\log\nN)^{\\xi} \\big]} \\] for $N$ large enough. (2) The proof of the {\\it Dyson's\nconjecture} \\cite{Dy} which states that the time scale of the Dyson Brownian\nmotion to reach local equilibrium is of order $N^{-1}$. (3) The edge\nuniversality holds in the sense that the probability distributions of the\nlargest (and the smallest) eigenvalues of two generalized Wigner ensembles are\nthe same in the large $N$ limit provided that the second moments of the two\nensembles are identical.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Jul 2010 09:44:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 26 Aug 2010 19:46:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 3 Dec 2010 20:32:20 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 16 Aug 2011 19:38:55 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sat, 17 Sep 2011 16:31:49 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Sun, 25 Sep 2011 19:17:07 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 26 Oct 2011 00:36:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-10-27"}
